com.gotenna.sdk.data.frequencies

Class GTFrequencyChannel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gotenna.sdk.data.frequencies.GTFrequencyChannel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<GTFrequencyChannel>

    public final class GTFrequencyChannel
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<GTFrequencyChannel>
    Represents a frequency channel that can be sent to the goTenna to configure what channels it operates on.

      • GTFrequencyChannel

        public GTFrequencyChannel(int frequencyHz,
                          boolean isControlChannel)
                   throws GTInvalidFrequencyChannelException
        Creates a frequency channel that can be sent to the goTenna.
        Parameters:
        frequencyHz - The frequency of the channel in hertz, must be [142Mhz - 175Mhz] or [445Mhz - 480Mhz]
        isControlChannel - Indicates whether this is a control channel or not
        Throws:
        GTInvalidFrequencyChannelException - When the frequency is not within the range of [142Mhz - 175Mhz] or [445Mhz - 480Mhz]

        public static boolean channelListsMatch(@NonNull
                                        java.util.List<GTFrequencyChannel> listA,
                                        @NonNull
                                        java.util.List<GTFrequencyChannel> listB)
        Determines if to different lists of frequency channels match each other. They match if the lists are the same size, and have exactly the same channels in the same order.
        Parameters:
        listA - A list of channels to check.
        listB - The other list of channels to check against.
        Returns:
        True is the lists match, false otherwise.
